Tesla Inc. TSLA, -2.72% stock skyrocketed 20% on Monday, ending at $780 and establishing a new record close and a new intraday high at $786.14. It was the stock's largest one-day percentage increase since May 9, 2013, when it rose 24.4%. Earlier Monday, analyst Bill Selesky at Argus Research upped his price target on the stock to $808, among the highest on Wall Street, saying that Tesla is ready to reap the benefits of its EV dominance. The company last week reported better-than-expected fourth-quarter profit and sales. Tesla shares have been on a tear since mid-December.
